Despite the stated intention to invest these funds to secure historic economic growth, it seems that the only growth sectors are repression, suffering, debt and corruption.
Monumental investment
The people strategically empowered to steward this monumental investment to achieve national transformation have forgotten themselves and embarked on frolics of their own.
Reports that the president’s directives are often disregarded with impunity indicate a cardinal instance of the emerging baronial insolence. On what conceivable basis could a bureaucrat contemplate disobeying the Head of State?
A key directive in question regards the adoption of an online procurement system. In the President’s own words, “This would enhance the highest level of public scrutiny at all units of public administration, and improve the management of public resources for public good”.



