But the facts suggest I haven’t scratched the surface of the problem. Some Sh635 billion lost through MDAs, and nary a voice raised in outrage or admonition by our ministers, who meanwhile continue to voraciously amass privilege, is a most damning report on the state of our nation.
All 47 counties were allocated Sh316 billion this year. This is the sort of money invested in the very visible transformation of our countryside, as well as the dramatic and scandalous excesses of our local leaders.
Through MDAs, we lose the equivalent of two years’ allocation to all counties to private pockets. Cartels consume twice every year what legitimate county governments get in one year.
Perhaps these cartels invest their proceeds in funds that subscribe in our international bonds, so that we keep paying them. Anglo Leasing was modelled that way: steal-lending. In any event, the kind of monster we are fattening with all this corruption is bound to be extremely devastating once it gets going.



